prise Victories\n| page =13\n| work= [[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LXII |issue=19044\n| date = 1925-06-15\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19250615.2.136.2\n| accessdate = 2019-09-11}}</ref>\n| away = Athletic\n| try1 = [[Clarrie Polson]], R Hargreaves 2, [[Wally Somers]] 2, R Stack, E Brown, A Clark\n| con1 = C Hand 6\n| pen1 = E Thompson\n| try2 = [[Ernie Herring]], Watkins, [[Bert Avery]]\n| con2 = [[Ernie Herring]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance =\n| referee = Hill\n}}\n\n======Round 9======\n[[Andrew O'Brien (rugby)|Jim O'Brien]] for Marist and [[Tom Haddon]] for Devonport were ordered off for fighting in their match at [[Carlaw Park]].\nIn one of the more amazing team efforts in early Auckland rugby league history the City team saw all 13 of its players score points in a 57-10 victory over Athletic. There were nine different try scorers and the four who didn\u2019t cross the line all kicked at least one conversion.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 June\n| time = 2:45\n| home = Devonport\n| score = 19-11\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Surprise By Devonport/Marist Old Boys Beaten\n| page = 12\n| work= [[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LXII |issue=19050\n| date = 1925-06-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19250622.2.131.1\n| accessdate = 2019-09-12}}</ref>\n| away = Marist\n| try1 = [[James Lawrence O\u2019Brien|Jim O\u2019Brien]], [[Tom Haddon]], [[Stan Webb (rugby league)|Stan Webb]]\n| con1 = J Laing\n| pen1 = [[Bert Laing]] 4\n| try2 = [[Hec Brisbane]], Malloy, Gallagher\n| con2 = [[Charles Gregory (rugby league)|Charles Gregory]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 9000\n| referee = Taylor\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 June\n| time = 2:45\n| home = City\n| score = 57-10\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Overwhelms Athletic\n| page = 12\n| work= [[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LXII |issue=19050\n| date = 1925-06-22\n| url =https://