r as a straight line on the graph. The [[slope]] of the straight line determines the rate of growth of the number of cases, with a steeper slope representing a higher growth rate.\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=0\n|width=900\n|height=350\n|colors = Orange, OrangeRed, SkyBlue, Black\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date (day/month)\n|xAxisAngle=-65\n|yAxisTitle=Total no. of cases (cumulative)\n|legend=Legend\n|y1Title=Confirmed\n|y2Title=Active\n|y3Title=Recovered\n|y4Title=Deaths\n<!-- To update the log plot, replace |x= to |y3= below by copying them from the above linear plot -->\n| x =  23/1, 24/1, 25/1, 26/1, 27/1, 28/1, 29/1, 30/1, 31/1, 1/2, 2/2, 3/2, 4/2, 5/2, 6/2, 7/2, 8/2, 9/2, 10/2, 11/2, 12/2, 13/2, 14/2, 15/2, 16/2, 17/2, 18/2, 19/2, 20/2, 21/2, 22/2, 23/2, 24/2, 25/2, 26/2, 27/2, 28/2, 29/2, 1/3, 2/3, 3/3, 4/3, 5/3, 6/3, 7/3, 8/3, 9/3, 10/3, 11/3, 12/3, 13/3, 14/3, 15/3, 16/3, 17/3, 18/3, 19/3, 20/3, 21/3, 22/3, 23/3, 24/3, 25/3, 26/3, 27/3, 28/3, 29/3, 30/3, 31/3, 1/4, 2/4, 3/4, 4/4, 5/4, 6/4, 7/4, 8/4, 9/4, 10/4, 11/4, 12/4, 13/4, 14/4, 15/4, 16/4, 17/4, 18/4, 19/4, 20/4, 21/4, 22/4\n| y1 = 1, 3, 3, 4, 5, 7, 10, 13, 16, 18, 18, 18, 24, 28, 30, 33, 40, 43, 45, 47, 50, 58, 67, 72, 75, 77, 81, 84, 85, 86, 89, 89, 90, 91, 93, 96, 98, 102, 106, 108, 110, 112, 117, 130, 138, 150, 160, 166, 178, 187, 200, 212, 226, 243, 266, 313, 345, 385, 432, 455, 509, 558, 631, 683, 732, 802, 844, 879, 926, 1000, 1049, 1114, 1189, 1309, 1375, 1481, 1623, 1910, 2108, 2299, 2532, 2918, 3252, 3699, 4427, 5050, 5992, 6588, 8014, 9125, 10141\n| y2 = 1, 3, 3, 4, 5, 7, 10, 13, 16, 18, 18, 18, 23, 27, 29, 31, 38, 37, 38, 38, 35, 43, 50, 54, 56, 53, 52, 50, 48, 39, 40, 38, 37, 33, 31, 30, 29, 30, 32, 30, 32, 33, 36, 48, 48, 60, 67, 73, 82, 91, 103, 107, 121, 134, 152, 196, 221, 254, 290, 309, 355, 401, 469, 509, 547, 602, 629, 648, 683, 752, 779, 827, 886, 983, 1025, 1098, 1211, 1443, 1609, 1763, 1964, 2323, 2631, 3037, 3734, 4331, 5241, 5809, 7202, 8275\n| y3 =